				The Super Bowl Indicator is a superstition that says that the stock markets performance in a given year can be predicted based on the outcome of the Super Bowl of that year It was discovered by Leonard Koppett in the 70s when he realized that it had never been wrong until that point This pseudomacroeconomic concept states that if a team from the American Football Conference AFC wins then it will be a bear market or down market but if a team from the National Football Conference NFC or a team that was in the NFL before the NFLAFL merger it will be a bull market up market



